text: Alfei Jürgenson was an Estonian professional footballer who played as a striker for the Estonian national football team. ==Career== He participated in the 1924 Paris Olympic Games with the Estonian football team. In 1924 until 1930, he played for JK Tallinn and played four games for Estonia. ==References== Category:1904 births Category:1947 deaths Category:Estonian footballers Category:Olympic footballers of Estonia Category:Footballers at the 1924 Summer Olympics Category:Association football forwards Category:Estonia international footballers
